  "market_context": "Friday 20 September session on EUR/USD 15-minute chart. Price had established an Asia range. London session began with an attempted breakout, but neither side of the Asia range could sustain a displacement, producing an indecision/doji daily candle consistent with a Seek and Destroy profile.",
  "key_observation": "London swept above the Asia range high with an aggressive move, then reversed back inside the range. Price then tested the opposite (low) side of the range but also failed to break out, repeatedly gravitating back to equilibrium and the daily open throughout the session.",
  "analysis_steps": [
    "Step 1: Marked out the Asia session high and low to define the Asia range on the EUR/USD 15-minute chart.",
    "Step 2: Observed London session price move outside the top of the Asia range, followed by an aggressive reversal back inside the range — no sustained bullish displacement.",
    "Step 3: Watched price trade to the opposite (low) side of the Asia range; noted it also failed to displace or break out to the downside.",
    "Step 4: Marked discount and premium of the Asia range and identified equilibrium (50% midpoint) as the gravitational target.",
    "Step 5: Extended the Asia range high/low and daily open lines across the rest of the session to track price behavior.",
    "Step 6: Observed price making a new low below the range; anticipated a return back into the initial range toward the daily open rather than a sustained breakdown.",
    "Step 7: Tracked discount and premium of the new leg lower as price continued to oscillate, confirming price returned to equilibrium and back into the initial Asia range.",
    "Step 8: Confirmed the daily candle closed as an indecision/doji, validating the Seek and Destroy profile and reinforcing the decision to stay out of the market on this day."
  ],
  "outcome": "No trade taken. The analyst identified this as a Seek and Destroy profile and used it as a lesson in recognizing when to stay out of the market rather than participating.",
  "lessons": "On Seek and Destroy days, price sweeps both sides of the Asia range without sustained directional expansion and continually reverts to equilibrium and the daily open. Recognizing this profile early prevents chasing false breakouts; the primary value is learning to avoid trading, not finding entries.",
